    <stitle>ALLISON WT TRANSMISSION ELECTRONIC CONTROLS - DESCRIPTION - VEHICLE INTERFACE MODULE (VIM)</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="2">
        <title>VEHICLE INTERFACE MODULE (VIM)</title>
        <para>The vehicle interface module (VIM) contains the ignition and battery power fuses which protect the WT
            Electronic Control System (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0800303">Figure 3</hotlnk>). The VIM also houses six relays used for controlling vehicle
            (or optional vehicle component) functions. The vehicle cab (or platform) harness and engine harness have
            connections to the transmission harness, which is connected to the VIM, the ECU and to the Allison WT
            transmission. Certain vehicle communications with the ECU go through the VIM as illustrated in
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0800304">Figure 4</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0800303" figsize="col-wide">
